* cat> [file name].txt == can write content in the file
* cat [file name].txt == shows the text content

* cat[file name1].txt [file name2].txt [file name3].txt == creating multiple text files at once.

* nano == is a text editor
* nano --version == find out which version is available in the system
* nano nano.txt == opens the text editor

* vi == is another popular text editor
* cat vi.txt == write content on vi file


* apt install == to install any packages 

*gedit == popular Linux tool
*sudo apt install gedit == installing the tool
